AB  - Public Significance Statement The current research aims to investigate the relationship between ethnic identification and support for minority rights among both minority and majority group members by examining how endorsing the minority group's conflict narrative may play an important role in this relationship. Our studies may pave the way for positive intergroup relations in conflict contexts by demonstrating how (a) ethnic identity (albeit depending on group status), (b) ally identity, and (c) minority group's conflict narratives may become facilitators to supporting policies that aim to improve the position of minority groups in society.
